      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "that makes sense, the vector thing is still a bit weird to visualize though. so with the inductor, is the \"opposition\" it provides constant? like, does it just sit there resisting the current, or is there something about how the reactance actually behaves in the circuit that makes it different from a standard resistor?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
